******
[4] Greece
Date: Mon 15 Oct 2018 19:58 EEST
Source: Ekathimerini.com [extracted, edited]
http://www.ekathimerini.com/233648/article/ekathimerini/news/nine-new-cases-of-measles-reported-in-greece


Health officials have identified 9 new cases of measles in the past 10 days, bringing the total number recorded since May 2017, when the latest outbreak of the illness was first reported, to 3258.

The 9 people infected, reportedly all members of the Roma community, are receiving treatment at Kilkis Hospital in northern Greece, the country's union of public hospital workers (POEDIN) said on [Mon 15 Oct 2018].

POEDIN said about 200 staff at hospitals have been diagnosed with the disease since the outbreak started.

