[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of the Philippines: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6095283,12906

The number of measles cases worldwide is increasing. [In August 2018 it was reported] that more than 41 000 people have been infected with measles in the World Health Organization's (WHO's) European Region for the 1st 6-months of 2018, already exceeding 12-month totals for any year this decade, the WHO Regional Office for Europe reported.

The previous European Region 12-month record was 23 927 cases for all of 2017, the WHO said.

According to these health officials, measles outbreaks are directly related to suboptimal vaccination coverage.

As an example, on 16 Jul 2018, the WHO reported only 4 EU/EEA countries have met the 95 percent vaccination goal for both doses of measles-containing vaccine during 2017.

Separately, the measles outbreak news in South America is equally concerning.

On 24 Jul 2018, the Pan American Health Organization (PAHO) latest update reported a total of 2472 confirmed cases of measles from 11 countries in the Americas so far this year [2018].

The majority of the 2018 measles cases occurred in Venezuela (1613 cases) and Brazil (1053), followed by the United States.

(Excerpted from https://www.precisionvaccinations.com/international-travelers-can-prevent-measles-outbreaks-mmr-vaccination). These data were reported in August 2018. The case numbers continue to increase. - Mod.LK]
